{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> χρύσεος</b>, η, ον, <br /> also ος, ον in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"“Anthologia Graeca” 5.30 (1st c.BC: Antipater Thessalonicensis Epigrammaticus)\">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>], <i>Attic dialect</i> <i>contraction</i> <b>χρυσοῦς</b>, ῆ, οῦν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “IG” 12.358.4, etc.\">Refs</a>]; <i>Epic dialect</i> <b>χρύσειος</b>, η, ον: [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus and 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus use both χρύσεος and -ειος, χρυσῇ is uncertain in 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 5.425 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; Lyric poetry used χρύσεος, α, ον, and this form sometimes occurs in Trag. dialogue and even in Prose, as [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Agesilaus” 5.5 codices, 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Lucullus” 37, 2nd c.AD: Apollodorus Damascenus Mechanicus 2.5.10, 2nd c.AD(?): Antoninus Liberalis Mythographus 36.1 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <i>Aeolic dialect</i> <b>χρύσιος</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 7th-6th c.BC: Sappho Lyrica 1.8, +others\">Refs 7th c.BC+</a>] (but χρύσεα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC: Theocritus Poeta Bucolicus 29.37)\">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]; <i>Boeotian dialect</i> <b>χρούσιος</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “SIG” 337.8 (4th c.BC)\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]: (χρυσός):—<b>golden,</b> frequently in <i>Epic dialect</i>, especially of what belonged to gods, χρυσέῳ ἐν δαπέδῳ, χρυσέοις δεπάεσσι, χρύσειον ἐπὶ θρόνον, etc., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 4.2, 3, 8.442, +others\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; χ. τάλαντα the <b>golden</b> scales of Zeus, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 22.209; χ. ἰτύς, ζυγόν, of Hera's chariot, 5.724, 730; ἱμάσθλη χ., of Zeus and Poseidon, 8.44 = 13.26 \">Refs</a>]; ζώνη χ., of Calypso and Circe, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 5.232 = 10.545, etc.\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; δόμος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 7th-6th c.BC: Sappho Lyrica \">Refs 7th c.BC+</a>] [prev. cited]; of possessions of mortals, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 4.133, 5.425, +others\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]: sometimes <b>enriched</b> or <b>adorned with gold,</b> χ. σκῆπτρον [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1.15, compare 246; μάχαιρα 18.598; θύραι 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 7.88 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; κλῖναι, κρητῆρες, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 9.82, 80 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἕστηκε.. Ἀλέξανδρος ὁ χ., of a statue, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 8.121; χρυσοῦς στάθητι 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Pseudol.” 15. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> χρύσεια μέταλλα <b>gold</b>-mines, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 4.105 (the only instance of χρύσειος in _Attic dialect_, compare χρυσεῖον). \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> χρυσοῦς (i.e. στατήρ), ὁ, <b>a gold coin,</b> ={στατήρ}, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “IG” 7.303.98, +others (Oropus, 3rd c.BC), “IPE” 12.32 A 13 (Olbia, 3rd c.BC), LXX.Gen.24.22, 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Pericles” 25 \">LXX+3rd c.BC+</a>] (in Papyrus, not a coin, but the equivalent of [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 20 silver drachmae, “PCair.Zen.” 28.11 (3rd c.BC), etc.)\">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]; χρυσοῖ ἐπίσημοι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 4.56.3, compare 2nd c.AD(?): Pollianus Epigrammaticus 9.53, 59, 5th c.AD(?): Hesychius Legal icographus \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__4</b></Level3> χρύσεον, τό, <b>gold plaque</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “SIG” 1122.7 (Selinus, 5th c.BC). \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>gold-coloured, golden-yellow,</b> ἔθειραι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 8.42, 13.24; χ. νέφη [prev. work] 523, etc.\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; ἀέρος κόμαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “Pae.” 6.137 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τῶν τὰ χρυσᾶ the <b>yolks</b> of eggs, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Athenaeus Epigrammaticus 9.376d. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> <i>metaphorically</i>, <b>golden,</b> χρυσέη Ἀφροδίτη [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 3.64, 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 8.337; Μοῖσα 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “I.” 8(7).5; σθένος ἀελίου χ. [prev. author] “P.” 4.144; ὦ χ. θύγατερ Διός 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 188 (Lyric poetry); Ἐλπίς [prev. work] 158 (Lyric poetry)\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; τιμή [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Ant.” 699; ὦ χρυσοῖ θεοί 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Ranae” 483; χ. ὑγίεια 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “P.” 3.73; λογισμοῦ ἀγωγή 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 645a; ἦθος 4th c.BC: Antiphanes Comicus 212.5; τὸ χ. ὀρνίθων γένος [prev. author] 175 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; χ. γένος ἀνθρώπων, of the [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Golden” Age, 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Opera et Dies” 109, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 468e, “Phdr.” 235e, “Cra.” 397e. \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__III.b</b></Level4> sometimes used ironically, ἐγὼ δὲ ὁ χ. but I, <b>fine fellow that I am</b>.., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Laps.” 1 \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]; Πλάτωνα χρυσοῦν (i.e. Ἐπίκουρος ἐκάλει) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.AD(?): Diogenes Laertius 10.8, compare 3rd c.BC(?): Menodotus Samius Historicus cited in 2nd c.AD: Galenus Medicus “Subf.Emp.” 63. \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__III.2</b></Level3> <b>wealthy,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.AD: Palaephatus Paradoxographus 31.4 (assuming variant). [χρῡσέη, χρῡσέην, χρῡσέου, χρῡσέῳ, etc., in 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>] must be pronounced as <i>disyllable</i>, as is fully proved by such passages as [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 1.15, 374: but Lyric Poets sometimes used ῠ in χρύσεος, 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “P.” 3.73, 4.4, 144, +others, 5th c.BC: Bacchylides Lyricus 9.6, 15.2 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; so also Trag., but only in Lyric poetry, not in Iambics or Anapaestics, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 157, 188, “Ant.” 103, 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Medea” 632, 978, “IA” 1051, “IT” 1253, “Tr.” 856, “Ba.” 372, “Heracl.” 916, “HF” 351, 396, “El.” 192; sometimes also Epigrammatists, “Anthologia Graeca” 6.292.2 (3rd c.BC: Hedylus Epigrammaticus), 7.233.1 (1st c.AD: Apollonides Epigrammaticus), 13.18.4 (from Parmeno), “APl.” 4.96.8.] \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G5552","accentedUnicode":"χρύσεος","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G5557","matchingForm":"χρυσός","stepTransliteration":"chrusos","gloss":"gold","_zh_tw_Gloss":"金子, 金","_es_Gloss":"oro","_zh_Gloss":"金子, 金"}],"shortDef":"golden","mediumDef":"golden <br />made of gold; same as G5997","stepGloss":"golden","stepTransliteration":"chruseos","count":18,"_es_Definition":"de oro","_zh_tw_Definition":"1) 金的<br>2) 金子做的<br>3) 金子鑲嵌或包裹的","_zh_Definition":"1) 金的<br>2) 金子做的<br>3) 金子镶嵌或包裹的","_step_Type":"word","_vi_Definition":"làm bằng vàng; vật phẩm được làm bằng vàng","_zh_tw_Gloss":"金","_es_Gloss":"de oro","_zh_Gloss":"金"}]}